data.name: Crispy Oven-Baked Potato Wedges
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously crispy potato wedges, seasoned to perfection, perfect for snacking or as a side dish.
detailedCookingInstructions: Wash and scrub the potatoes, then cut them into wedges.
In a large bowl, toss the potato wedges with olive oil until evenly coated.
Sprinkle salt, black pepper, garlic powder, and paprika over the wedges, mixing well to ensure even coverage.
Spread the wedges in a single layer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake for 25-30 minutes, flipping halfway through, until golden and crispy.
If desired, sprinkle grated parmesan cheese on top during the last 5 minutes of baking for extra flavor.
